NAME
----
ubi - universal binary wrapper for multi-platform executables

SYNOPSIS
--------
ubi [-o <output>] [-v] [-h] [<exec>...]
ubi inspect <binary>
ubi add <binary> <exec>...
ubi remove <binary> <exec>...

DESCRIPTION
-----------
UBI is a tool for creating, merging, inspecting, and executing universal binaries that contain
multiple platform-specific executables (e.g., Mach-O, ELF) in a single file. It enables seamless
cross-platform distribution and execution.

FEATURES
--------
- Merge multiple platform executables into a single universal binary
- Inspect contents and architectures of universal binaries
- Add or remove architectures/sections from existing binaries
- Fast extraction and execution with caching
- Supports ELF (Linux), Mach-O (macOS), and fat binaries (macOS universal)
- Command-line interface similar to Unix tools

USAGE EXAMPLES
--------------

aarch64-linux-musl-cc -o linux-aarch64 main.c
x86_64-linux-musl-cc -o linux-x86_64 main.c
clang -o darwin-aarch64 main.c   # On macOS, use clang to build for Apple Silicon

# Combine the platform-specific executables into a single universal binary
ubi -o main darwin-aarch64 linux-aarch64 linux-x86_64

# Run the universal binary directly (if ubi is installed)
./main

# Or, for testing without installing, prepend the current directory to PATH
PATH="$(pwd):$PATH" ./main

# View the architectures and executables included in the universal binary
ubi inspect main

